[Something wrong here. Is the State of Alabama using horses and
emus as sentinels for predicting the presence of infected
mosquitoes? Surely there is a vector control program there that
would provide greater predictive capabilities.
It is certanly a good idea to decrease mosquito breeding sites but
the focus should be on sites where the vectors breed.
Question: If there are four 6-packs in a case, how many cases are
there in a rash? - Mod CHC
